decks.notes: This deck focuses on assembling a fast combo win without relying on traditional land cards. By using powerful cards like Flare of Denial and Disrupting Shoal to control the opponent's plays, combined with cards like Thundertrap Trainer and Hydroelectric Specimen to generate advantage, the deck aims to set up a lethal finisher with Goblin Charbelcher. The inclusion of cards like Whir of Invention and Tameshi, Reality Architect offer additional flexibility and consistency to the combo strategy, while protecting it with counters like Pact of Negation and Force of Negation.

This deck focuses on assembling the UrzaTron lands to generate a large amount of mana to cast powerful Eldrazi creatures such as Emrakul, the Promised End and Thought-Knot Seer. The deck also includes cards that can disrupt the opponent's game plan, such as All Is Dust and Karn, the Great Creator, while providing card advantage with The Underworld Cookbook. The goal is to control the board and overwhelm the opponent with high-impact threats.
